article.headline: Sacred Heart 71, St. Francis (Pa.) 68
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. -- Shane Gibson scored 26 points, hitting four free throws in the final 26 seconds, as Sacred Heart held off St. Francis (Pa.) 71-68 Thursday night to snap a three-game Northeast Conference skid. The Pioneers (8-10, 2-3) shot a season-high 56.1 percent (23 of 41) to overcome 22 turnovers. Gibson made 9 of 12 field goals and also had five of Sacred Heart's season-high 12 steals. The Pioneers led by eight in the first half, but only 35-34 at halftime. After the Red Flash (3-13, 2-3) used a 6-0 spurt to lead 50-45 with 14:32 remaining, Sacred Heart pulled ahead 61-53. But the Pioneers didn't make a basket for the next 5:29 and St. Francis tied it at 62 with 2:28 left. Phil Gaetano's 3-pointer and six free throws allowed Sacred Heart to hold on despite a pair of 3s by Anthony Ervin, who led the Red Flash with 14 points.
